This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with unsupervised dictionary learning for image recognition. It may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the use of clustering algorithms for feature learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it pertains to the development of intelligent systems for image recognition. Neural networks (cs.NE) is another possible category as the paper discusses the pooling stage in early vision architectures. Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is a possible category as the paper deals with image feature learning.
